The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, May 06, 2003  Business Briefs New Delhi, May 5:The Centres direct  tax collection was up 20.39 per cent at Rs 82,071 crore  during 2002-03 compared with Rs 68,170 crore in 2001-02.  It was due to an impressive 27 per cent surge in corporation  tax collection. Corporation tax mop up grew 27 per cent  to Rs 46,266 crore during the last fiscal compared with  Rs 36,427 crore in 2001-02. Income tax collection was up  12.8 per cent at Rs 35,805 crore during the last fiscal  compared with Rs 31,742 crore in the previous fiscal. Calcutta, May 5:The Calcutta High Court  today adjourned till May 15 an appeal by the Jessop staff  association against an earlier order that said the company  was not in the strategic sector. Mumbai, May 5:BSES Ltd has mandated  ABN AMRO Bank, Citigroup Global Markets, Singapore Merchant  Bank Ltd, Rabobanks Singapore branch and Standard Chartered  Bank to arrange a five-year $ 100 million foreign currency  term loan. New Delhi, May 5:Sanjay Rishi has been  appointed as senior vice-president of service network partners  division of American Express Company.
